U.S. Total Baker Hughes Rig Count Rises to 28-Month High

-- B y   M a r g o t   H a b i b y
-- 
2011-04-29T19:26:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/u-s-total-baker-hughes-rig-count-rises-to-28-month-high-2-.html
Oil and natural gas rigs operating
in the U.S. rose to the highest level since December 2008 as  oil
prices  climbed to a 31-month high this week, according to data
published by  Baker Hughes Inc. (BHI)   The combined rig count rose by 18 to 1,818, the highest
level since Dec. 5, 2008, Baker Hughes said today on its
 website . The count reached a 22-year high of 2,031 in August
2008. Most of the increase this week was in Oklahoma and
 Pennsylvania .  Oil rigs jumped by 13 to 926 in the week ending April 29,
the highest level since Baker Hughes began issuing separate
counts for oil and gas rigs in 1987. Natural gas rigs rose by
four to 882, gaining for the first time in four weeks.  Crude for June delivery rose $1.07, or 1 percent, to
$113.93 a barrel, the highest settlement since Sept. 22, 2008,
on the  New York Mercantile Exchange . Futures gained 6.8 percent
in April, an unprecedented eighth straight monthly increase.
Prices have climbed 1.5 percent this week and 34 percent in the
past year.  Gas for June delivery rose 12.7 cents, or 2.8 percent, to
$4.698 per million British thermal units on the Nymex. Futures
gained 6.5 percent this week, 7 percent in April and 18 percent
in the past year.  Baker Hughes also reported that miscellaneous rigs, which
primarily drill for geothermal energy, rose by one to 10.  Rigs on land increased by 15 to 1,769. Rigs in inland
waters rose by two to 20.  The total rig count for offshore production rose by one to
29 as the Gulf of  Gulf of Mexico  added one rig to 28.  Canadian rigs fell by 10 to 133.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Margot Habiby in  Dallas  at   mhabiby@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at   dstets@bloomberg.net . 